div.p:
I have formerly recited the words of Melch. Canus, one of their great Biſhops, ſaying 
                  [Loc. Theolog. li. 6. c. 7. fol. 201. Not only the Greeks, but almoſt ALL THE REST OF THE BISHOPS OF THE WHOLE WORLD have vehemently fought to deſtroy the priviledge of the Church of Rome. And indeed they had on their ſide both the Arms of Emperours, and the GREATER NUMBER OF CHURCHES; 
               and yet they could never prevail to abrogate the Power of the one Pope of Rome.
